Morocco ' s CGEM business group re - appoints president . Morocco ' s CGEM business confederation on Thursday re - appointed wealthy businessman Abderrahim Lahjouji as its president , a spokesman said . " Lahjouji , who was the only candidate , was re - appointed for three years by a majority of 430 votes while 30 members abstained , " the spokesman for the Confederation Generale des Entreprises du Maroc ( CGEM ) said . Lahjouji , 55 , is also the managing - director of SOTRAVO , a leading contruction firm in Morocco . 
